In the afternoon, the visit will culminate in a ceremony at which Obama will receive a prestigious award.
He will be the fourth president of the United States, but only the third to win the award directly in office.
The White House has already announced that Obama will be talking about the Afghan war when he accepts the award.
The president does not want to avoid this issue, because he realizes that he is taking the prize as president, who is currently at war in two countries.
The war effort a few days ago increased by sending more troops to Afghanistan, which will not forget to highlight any of its critics.
At the ceremony, Obama will also receive a gold medal, a diploma and a cheque for ten million Swedish crowns (about 24 million Czech crowns).
He intends to put on charitable purposes, but has not yet decided on a specific charity.
