This decision confirms that there is indeed a process going on in the case, which can be described as the family saga of one of the richest families in France, in which mother and daughter attack each other and fight for the control of the L'Oréal cosmetic empire.
However, the 15th criminal court also ordered a medical examination of 87-year-old Liliana Bettencourt, which should be carried out by a college of three doctors.
The heir and main shareholder of L'Oréal has always refused to undergo such an investigation, certainly not under the conditions offered by the Public Prosecutor's Office in Nanterre during the investigation.
