New Instruments for Appreciation of Cars
These days, storms and accidents don’t just make car service.
Every day thousands of cars that have suffered an insurance incident are pulled into the service, where the expert must estimate the damage and the cost of repair.
No insurance event is the same and calculating the cost of parts and labor time can be a long and complicated job.
Calculate manually the repair costs from 20,000 to 30,000 euros including parts and labor can take two or three hours.
However, with the support of new computer tools it would be a matter of minutes
Therefore, almost 100% of experts use this type of system.
Service providers and solutions for estimating insurance events and maintenance are dedicated to collecting information provided by manufacturers to then develop and offer their customers a useful tool.
In Spain Audatex, from the American group Solera is the leading company; 80% of the evaluation is carried out with its products.
Other companies competing in the field of appraisal and information development tools are GtMotive and Eurotax.
Working with the data provided by manufacturers is not easy at all.
According to Eduard Vel<0xC3><0xA1>zquez, Audatex’s sales director, 63 manufacturers and importers work in Spain, each providing them with information in a different format.
In addition, the amount of data to be processed is still growing, as more versions, variants and engine solutions have been introduced in the last five years than in the previous fifteen years.
As soon as the new vehicle enters the market, these companies will start operating.
It is a very hot job, because it is necessary to catalog each of the thousands of parts of the vehicle and determine its price.
In addition, "intelligent" graphic processing is carried out on each model, where it is possible to "push out" individual parts of tourist cars.
As for the model with massive sales, the work can be done in a week if the process is very fast.
As for a minority car, it can take three or four months. Currently, Audatex has complete information on 99.2% of cars sold in Spain.
The most exclusive models they have information about include Porsche, but not Ferrari or Lamborghini, for example.
With regard to the rolling stock in circulation, they exceed 99%.
To perform the work of documentation and development of databases, Audatex has eight centers distributed around the world (Spain, France, Germany, USA, Brazil, Mexico, China and Japan) and each of them specializes in specific brands.
The national headquarters is in Alcobendas (Madrid).
There, more than a hundred technicians (normally mechanics) work simultaneously with three computer screens.
Audatex invests <0xE2><0x82><0xAC>90 million annually in the development of these databases.
