According to the Spanish law, a car whose chassis number has been discontinued cannot return to service, but can be used as a source of spare parts that have not been damaged.
Vehicles with historical value may be allowed to operate, even if they have been decommissioned, after a preliminary procedure.
Budgeting the service in four steps
With the Auda-Taller tool, Audatex guarantees that the user receives a budget in only four steps: identifying the vehicle, finding a spare part, creating a budget for budget generation.
Ease of use is an essential condition for these systems, especially for older professionals who are more or less reluctant to use new management techniques.
The database contains 1,034 vehicles, including 666 tourist vehicles, 109 off-road vehicles, 137 motorcycles, 78 vans and 44 trucks.
Naturally, for use you need a computer with an internet connection.
After identifying the model to be repaired, using the chassis number, a real graphical view of the model appears, and then the necessary spare part is selected.
The user can include variables such as the price of labor, surcharges or discounts, and then print and hand over to the customer.
AudaTaller is not an awarding tool like AudaPlus, but rather a reference catalogue.
The main difference between the two systems is that it is service-oriented and does not include an estimate of the workforce.
The cost of using this tool for the workshop is 350 euros per year, which the customer can finance.
Currently, Audatex is working to make these views three-dimensional.
This is an innovation that mechanics welcome, as it will allow, for example, to select a door and turn it to show the inside.
